reek partners the country’s newest search fund the fund so named because it’s a street name near the campus they attended has raised seed capital from individual and institutional investors and is now seeking an acquisition a process that could take up to two years “we have funding for the next two years and we can call on capital from the group of investors for the acquisition” said ansari whose website details the individual and corporate investors john hunkin and paul rogers former senior executives at cibc in toronto and new york respectively are two notable canadian investors while hunkin is a first time search fund investor rogers is a veteran his firm rhv capital has invested in  search funds rogers said the decision to invest is based on understanding the “motivations” of the entrepreneurs behind the search fund “it is a risky thing to do and we want to ensure that they have thought through all of the pros and cons next we try to assess if they could actually run a business” said rogers adding he has seen lau in action “he tackled a tough strategic issue with insight and precision rameez is a remarkable individual having been an entrepreneur in pakistan prior to going to stanford” but more importantly rogers said they are “both humble guys who want to continually listen and learn” and both want to be more than investors they want to run a business – the second element to the search fund model “we both have a passion for operations” said lau added ansari “our aspiration is to run a company” search funds raise capital a little differently from other investment funds the capital raising occurs in two rounds with the first raise earmarked to run an office and allow ansari and lau to seek out an acquisition and the latter round to fund the purchase of a business as is the norm with any private company there is a markup between the price paid by the initial investors — who have rights of first refusal when an acquisition is presented to them — and all subsequent investors to find the acquisition ansari who worked with boston consulting group and lau who has worked with cpp investment board and td securities will use two approaches they will call on middlemen lawyers and accountants with contacts in the private company world and from their own research into industries they like the targets will be chosen because of their industry business and financial characteristics as well the owner must be seeking a way to reduce his role in the company a typical target would have  million —  million in revenue be profitable with steady cash flows and not overly complex “industry growth is the key” said ansari “because macro dominates micro” search funds started at stanford about four decades back but until recently hadn’t made much of dent in canada now there are at least two handfuls of such investment firms a number of which have bought business and are now running them  comments share your thoughts news videos fp street home capital repays  billion line of credit from berkshire hathaway four years ago omers bought civica for 63 million today it sold it for 7 billion couchetard wows with firsttime us billion debt offering online lender borrowell raises  million in latest funding round tembecs largest shareholder says more than half will vote against the takeover how bill downe turned yearold bmo from laggard to leader nvcc debt gets its due with fixedincome index inclusion exchange income reports higher earnings but shares fall amid shortseller criticism regulators asked to weigh in to ensure fair vote on tembec takeover blockbuster avista deal lifts hydro one into top  utilities on continent tembec takeover could come down to ‘empty voting’ will a closer scrutiny stop the sale of sandvine corp from getting over the line top stories ‘a tragedy for canada’ petronas cancels b lng project as bc jacks up demands with energy prices collapsing globally and the business in bc having a tough time remaining viable pacific northwest lng needed l